<OrderOfTheHouse><Num></Num><OrderDate><Text><?start-line?>Order of the House [19 NOVEMBER 2012]</Text>

</OrderDate>
<?new-line?><OrderPreamble><Text><?start-line?>That the following provisions shall apply to the Groceries Code Adjudicator Bill <?new-line?>[<Emphasis>Lords</Emphasis>]:</Text>

<?new-line?>

</OrderPreamble>
<?new-line?><OrderText><Pblock>
<Title><?start-line?>Committal</Title>
</Pblock>
<P1>
<Pnumber>1.</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<Text><?start-line?>The Bill shall be committed to a Public Bill Committee.</Text>
</P1para>
</P1>

<?new-line?><Pblock>
<Title><?start-line?>Proceedings in Public Bill Committee</Title>
</Pblock>
<P1>
<Pnumber>2.</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<Text><?start-line?>Proceedings in the Public Bill Committee shall (so far as not previously <?new-line?>concluded) be brought to a conclusion on Thursday 6 December 2012.</Text>
</P1para>
</P1>
<P1>
<Pnumber>3.</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<Text><?start-line?>The Public Bill Committee shall have leave to sit twice on the first day on <?new-line?>which it meets.</Text>
</P1para>
</P1>

<?new-line?><Pblock>
<Title><?start-line?>Consideration and Third Reading</Title>
</Pblock>
<P1>
<Pnumber>4.</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<Text><?start-line?>Proceedings on Consideration shall (so far as not previously concluded) be <?new-line?>brought to a conclusion one hour before the moment of interruption on the <?new-line?>day on which those proceedings are commenced.</Text>
</P1para>
</P1>
<P1>
<Pnumber>5.</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<Text><?start-line?>Proceedings on Third Reading shall (so far as not previously concluded) be <?new-line?>brought to a conclusion at the moment of interruption on that day.</Text>
</P1para>
</P1>
<P1>
<Pnumber>6.</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<Text><?start-line?>Standing Order No. 83B (Programming committees) shall not apply to <?new-line?>proceedings on Consideration and Third Reading.</Text>
</P1para>
</P1>

<?new-line?><Pblock>
<Title><?start-line?>Other proceedings</Title>
</Pblock>
<P1>
<Pnumber>7.</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<Text><?start-line?>Any other proceedings on the Bill (including any proceedings on <?new-line?>consideration of any message from the Lords) may be programmed.</Text>
</P1para>
</P1>

</OrderText>
